          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": "invgamma"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " takes "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "a"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " as a shape parameter for "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineMath",
              "value": "a"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": "invgamma"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " is a special case of "
            },
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": "gengamma"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " with "
            },
            {
              "type": "inlineCode",
              "value": "c=-1"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ", and it is a different parameterization of the scaled inverse chi-squared distribution. Specifically, if the scaled inverse chi-squared distribution is parameterized with degrees of freedom "
